Author: ODI Version: 0.9 Last Update: FEB-2008
Description : - Integrates data in any ISO-92 compliant database target table in truncate / insert (append) mode. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled. - When loading data to the target, this KM also populates PK/GUID XRef table on a separate database
Important restrictions for ESB XREF usage:
This IKM : - assumes that it is used in conjunction with the LKM SQL to SQL (ESB XREF) - uses a hard coded logical schema ESB_XREF that points to the Oracle instance that holds the XREF_DATA table
USE UD1 to mark columns you want to populate with the COMMON ID calculated from XREF
Other standard restrictions: - When working with journalized data, if the "Synchronize deletions from journal" is executed, the deleted rows on the target are committed regardless of the COMMIT option - The TRUNCATE option is not implemented on all RDBMs - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - When using the RECYCLE_ERRORS option, you have to set an Update Key for your interface. - When using this module with a journalized source table, data are automatically filtered to not include source deletions. - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Commit all data inserted in the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected from a previous control.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Table Name to use in the XREF table
MANDATORY: Table Name to use in the XREF table. Example: ORDERS
MANDATORY: Primary key column name to use as a literal in the XREF table
Expression to populate the row num.
Load PKs and GUIDS to remote PK tab
select SKEY_VAL PK_VAL, SYSGUID GUID_VAL from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%>

/* Retrieve exisiting PK/GUID values from remote XREF table */ select PK_VAL, GUID_VAL from <%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", "PK$" + odiRef.getOption("XREF_TABLE_NAME"), "W")%> where ROW_NUMBER is not null

merge into <%=odiRef.getObjectName("XREF_DATA")%> T using ( select '<%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_TABLE_NAME")%>' XREF_TABLE_NAME, TWOROWS.COLUMN_NAME XREF_COLUMN_NAME, S.ROW_NUMBER ROW_NUMBER, min(case when TWOROWS.COLUMN_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_COLUMN_NAME")%>' then S.PK_VAL else S.GUID_VAL end) VALUE, 'N' IS_DELETED, '<@= java.lang.System.currentTimeMillis().toString() @>' LAST_DATE from (select '<%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_COLUMN_NAME")%>' COLUMN_NAME from dual union select 'COMMON' from dual) TWOROWS, <%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", "PK$" + odiRef.getOption("XREF_TABLE_NAME"), "W")%> S group by '<%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_TABLE_NAME")%>', TWOROWS.COLUMN_NAME, S.ROW_NUMBER ) S on ( T.XREF_TABLE_NAME = S.XREF_TABLE_NAME and T.XREF_COLUMN_NAME = S.XREF_COLUMN_NAME and T.ROW_NUMBER = S.ROW_NUMBER) when matched then update set T.IS_DELETED = S.IS_DELETED, T.LAST_MODIFIED = S.LAST_DATE, T.LAST_ACCESSED = S.LAST_DATE when not matched then insert ( T.XREF_TABLE_NAME, T.XREF_COLUMN_NAME, T.ROW_NUMBER, T.VALUE, T.IS_DELETED, T.LAST_MODIFIED, T.LAST_ACCESSED) values (S.XREF_TABLE_NAME, S.XREF_COLUMN_NAME, S.ROW_NUMBER, S.VALUE, S.IS_DELETED, S.LAST_DATE, S.LAST_DATE)

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
Drop remote PK Table on XREF DB
Update remote PK with existing GUID

update <%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", "PK$" + odiRef.getOption("XREF_TABLE_NAME"), "W")%> T set (GUID_VAL, ROW_NUMBER) = ( select min(case when S.XREF_COLUMN_NAME = 'COMMON' then S.VALUE else null end) GUID_VAL, S.ROW_NUMBER from XREF_DATA S where XREF_TABLE_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_TABLE_NAME")%>' group by XREF_TABLE_NAME, ROW_NUMBER having T.PK_VAL = min(case when S.XREF_COLUMN_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_COLUMN_NAME")%>' then S.VALUE else null end) ) where (PK_VAL) in ( select VALUE from XREF_DATA where XREF_TABLE_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_TABLE_NAME")%>' and XREF_COLUMN_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_COLUMN_NAME")%>' )
Assign new rownums to non-exist. PK
update <%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", "PK$" + odiRef.getOption("XREF_TABLE_NAME"), "W")%> set ROW_NUMBER = <%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_ROWNUMBER_EXPRESSION")%> where ROW_NUMBER is null

<%if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_METHOD"))){%> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%>, SYSGUID, SKEY_VAL ) select <%=snpRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ",\n\t", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%>, <%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_SYS_GUID_EXPRESSION")%>, SKEY_VAL from <%=snpRef.getFrom()%> where <% if (snpRef.getPop("HAS_JRN").equals("0")) { %> (1=1) <%} else {%> JRN_FLAG <> 'D' <% } %> <%=snpRef.getJoin()%> <%=snpRef.getFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=snpRef.getHaving()%>

<%if ( snpRef.getUserExit("FLOW_CONTROL").equals("1") ) { %> insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW")%> ) select <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> E where not exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= E.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "UK")%> ) and E.ORIGIN = '<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ERR_TYPE = '<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>' <% } %>
Drop remote PK Table on XREF DB
Create remote PK Table on XREF DB
create table <%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", "PK$" + odiRef.getOption("XREF_TABLE_NAME"), "W")%> ( PK_VAL varchar2(250) not null primary key , GUID_VAL varchar2(50) null, ROW_NUMBER varchar2(50) null )

/* This step applies all mappings to the target table */ /* Columns marked as UD1 are populated using the calculated COMMON_ID retrieved from the XREF table */ insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW and not UD1 and not TRG")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW and not UD1 and TRG")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",", "[COL_NAME] /* COMMON ID */", ",
	", "", "UD1")%> ) select <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW and not UD1 and not TRG")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW and not UD1 and TRG")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",", "SYSGUID", ",
	", "", "UD1")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%>
